I would like to get in on this debate. But after this post, lets take it
to non rpg email.

Anyway, I dont know whats up with that game, but Sting has never been in
WWF. I have is biography. He started in the indies, and then went to
Gerogia Championship Wrestling of the National Wrestling Alliance. He
has been there ever since, because Georgia Championship Wrestling became
World Championship Wrestling.

And KSL, you had to go insult WCW, the promotion that made me a fan. I
got into wrestling, watching WCW with my dad in 93. They have the most
amazing star and have always been the better promotion. You say they
have no talent, well DDP and Booker T. are the only extreamly good stars
they have now. But lets talk about AOL/Time Warner WCW.
Kevin Nash, Scott Hall, Bret Hart, Chris Benoit, Chris Jericho, Scott
Steiner, Rick Steiner, Arn Anderson, Ricky Steamboat, Sting, Curt
Hening, Rey Masterio Jr., Billy Kidman, Road Warriors, Dusty Rhodes,
Hulk Hogan, and the greatest wrestler of all time, the Nature Boy Ric
Flair. Of course there are many I didn't mention.

Oh you dont know who Scott Steiner is, KSL? Well he signed with WWF and
should show up in a few months. You should be amazed. He got the mic
skills, and as far as physical shape goes, there is not one man in WWF,
WCW, or ECW that can match up.
